import { useState } from "react" let Login=()=>{ let[user,setUser]=useState({email:"",password:""}) let emailHandler=(event)=>{ setUser({...user,email:event.target.value}) } let passwordHandler=(event)=>{ setUser({...user,password:event.target.value}) } let submitHandler=(event)=>{ console.log(user) } return

{JSON.stringify(user)}

} export default Login
